# UI Editing Consistency

Use `view-architecture-pattern.mdc` as canonical for editable-view layout and behavior.

This rule keeps only editing-flow specifics:

- Default flow is explicit `Edit` -> `Save` / `Cancel` (read-only otherwise).
- Avoid autosave unless explicitly requested; if requested, scope autosave to the requested subsection only.
- For read-only rendering, show case identifiers as plain values (not disabled textboxes).
- Reuse shared button/table classes and existing row-based DnD table pattern unless a feature explicitly requires otherwise.
